Actress Tonto Dikeh has reacted after being called out by her colleague, Ada Karl over an unpaid 15-year debt. Dikeh explained that Karl only offered her assistance as a little girl at the time. The mother of one, boasting about her ‘rich’ status, urged Karl to quit being ‘bitter’ and send account details to her management for ‘repayment’ of all the favours done her in the past. Tonto Dikeh wrote: “Ada Ada, you still bitter like this? If them leave me, you fit beat me? I don’t owe you jack, 15 years ago you helped a little girl (me). If you want payback, you say it.   Northern youths ask Emefiele to run for 2023 presidency     Oyedeji not our Reps consensus candidate, says Oke-Ogun PDP…     2023: Why we must support Tinubu – ACF Chieftain   “I AM RICH RICH NOW. If dem leave you, you fit beat me? Girl, not even with my hand-tied!!! “You need to heal girl. Thanks, like I always say, for looking out for me. You can send your account details to my management. “Have a good life Ada. I promise you, you’re gonna heal. Just open your heart to the process. “My question to you is, how deep is your PAIN, from 1-100? Lmaoo 80k since 15years ago. #PEACEOUT.”